{
  "stem": "5654.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to be very careful, because we could be denounced.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it got-- it kept on getting worse and worse as time went by.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We saw German patrol coming on horses in that area.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somehow, they didn't know there was a Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or maybe-- I, I have an idea that the French police just kept them away from us, you see?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were there till 1943.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How, as a little boy of six and seven, were you aware that you shouldn't be seen by Germans or--",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they, they kept on telling us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, you know, I think we learned that the Germans were, were-- well, when I found out that my parents were taken to a camp-- my, my father was taken-- was taken to camp, and the family.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we heard stories of other boys and girls, of their parents.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we realized we have to be very careful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were speaking Yiddish-- fluent Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they told us not to speak Yiddish, to continue to, to speak French and to be very careful not to speak Yiddish when we used to go on excursions.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Often, we used to go on excursions, you know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, we didn't wear yarmulkes because-- we only wore beret, which is the norm in France.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, inside the dining hall, we'd wear our yarmulkes for eating.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember that sometimes-- I was quite friendly with Mr.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Cogon, who used to gather the food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He used to go from farm to farm to get milk and supplies.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he had-- you know, he was driving to the farms to pick up the vegetables.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, we were assigned to pick up milk in these huge-- what do they call it?",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
